column5: no wonder I'm not getting anything on the upper, that pig ate them all!
I guess thats why I continue to fish the Upper...
Last time we fished there it was our best day of musky fishing ever and there was no one there but us.

This fish was taken by Howard Wagner recently from the upper Niagara River.  It weighed in at 53 1/2 lbs and had a girth of 28 inches.  Howard is one of Pennsylvania's top musky men and released the fish.
That pig is soo fat poor Howard probably couldnt stand up for a pic even if he wanted to..  Nice fattie!!
Congratulations Howard!!!!!!!!!!!  A real brute there!
nice ski... i have only seen them THAT size in my dreams  lol
Thanks Phil, that big girl is a definate trophy and I hope she's still playful this coming Saturday
WOW!    & ya know ya they say, there is allways one bigger then the last one you see
Nice fatty..
Wow...I can only dream!!! Awesome post...
WOW

I would like to say it was a Muskie Magnet but it wasn't.  Howard is stopping by to pick up our new short line trolling prototypes for testing I'll ask him when I see him and post it for all to see.
